{"id":892007143,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"3 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1675601295,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"27 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/892007143/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"37 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * struct TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode *left;\n *     TreeNode *right;\n *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}\n * };\n */\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    void inorder(TreeNode* root, vector<int>& in) {\n        if(root == NULL) return;\n        inorder(root->left, in);\n        in.push_back(root->val);\n        inorder(root->right, in);\n    }\n\n    bool findTarget(TreeNode* root, int k) {\n        vector<int> in;\n        inorder(root, in);\n\n        int left = 0, right = in.size()-1;\n        while(left < right) {\n            if(in[left] + in[right] == k) return true;\n            else if(in[left] + in[right] < k) left++;\n            else right--;\n        }\n\n        return false;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst","has_notes":false}
